               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Malkǝʾa samāʿtāta Ṗarāqliṭos “Image of the Martyrs of Ṗarāqliṭos”
                     (fols. 76ra-79ra): 32 strophes, incomplete.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="76ra" to="79ra"/>
                     <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5879ImageParaqlitos">Malkǝʾa samāʿtāta Ṗarāqliṭos: 32 strophes
                     </title>
                     <note>- The text is incomplete (at the 32nd strophe), the same as in Mss.<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap046">AP-046</ref>and<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap019">AP-019</ref>.</note>
                     <note>The manuscript probably continues <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap019">AP-019</ref></note>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>Made of <measure unit="leaf">12.0</measure> folios, of which
                              <measure unit="leaf" type="blank"/> blank 73r-75v, 79rb-84v, in
                              <measure unit="quire">1.0</measure> quires . 
                           
                           <note>- <locus from="73r" to="75v">73r-75v</locus>, 79rb-84v: blank folios not
                              ruled; <locus target="#73">73</locus> and 84 probably used as protective
                              leaves.</note>
                           
                           <dimensions type="outer">
                              <height unit="mm">210</height>
                              <width unit="mm">158</width>
                              <depth unit="mm">7</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>In the Ms.,
                           the foliation starts from the number 73 (the Ms. has been foliated and
                           photographed together with other fragments).</foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <list>
                              <item xml:id="q1">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">12</dim>
                                 <locus target="#12"/>
                                 <locus from="73r" to="84v"/>I(12/fols. 73r-84v).</item>
                           </list>
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. is without boards and unbound; the sewing
                           in the centre fold is not visible.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="24">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>154</height>
                              <width>113</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">9</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">18</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">36</dim>
                              <dim type="right">22</dim>
                              <dim type="left">11</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">9</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>All data for <locus target="#77r">77r</locus>
                           </note>
                           <ab type="ruling">the number of lines changes: e.g., 22 in <locus target="#77r">77r</locus>, 24 in <locus target="#76r">76r</locus>
                              and 26 in <locus target="#78r">78r</locus>.</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking and ruling are not visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern:  1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Primary pricks are not visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are not visible (except on <locus target="#73r">73r</locus> and 84r). </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is written above the ruling. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written below the ruling (?). </ab>

                           <ab type="ruling"> The scribe disregarded the ruling: he doesn’t write on
                              the ruled lines.</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (brilliant red).</seg>
                        <date>First half of the 20th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">The name of the protagonists samāʿtāta Ṗarāqliṭos; a
                           few lines alternating with black lines in the incipit page of the text;
                           the word salām; elements of the punctuation signs, of corrections and of
                           decorations around the word hǝräy at the text margins.</seg>
                        <note>- The handwriting seems to be the same as in<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESap019#h1">AP-019</ref>.</note>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">On <locus target="#78va">78va</locus>
                        l.20, the letter ጵ has the 6th order marker set up on the vertical stroke at
                        the top, oriented to the left; the same, in the same word and passage, is in
                        Mss. AP-046 (<locus target="#43ra">43ra</locus> l.3) and AP-019 (<locus target="#20rb">20rb</locus>
                        l.7).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The word ህረይ፡ (with red and black decorations around) is written at the margins of the text on fols. 77r and 79r (s. the same in Ms. AP-019, e.g., <locus target="#46va">fol.  46va</locus>). - Titles, መልክአ ሰማዕታት and ዘሰማዕታት መልክአ, are crudely written in pen in a recent hand on fols. 75r and 83r. - Immediate correction marked by lines and red dots above and below the word on <locus target="#77v">fol.  77v</locus>. - Crude recent notes in pen in the upper margin of <locus target="#76r">fol.  76r</locus> and within the text (as corrections) on fols. 76ra, 76rb, 78rb and 78vb.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">No boards. No sewing.</decoNote>
